            . I am a <rs id="t18200628-177-viclabel969" type="occupation">labourer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200628-177-victim1514 t18200628-177-viclabel969"></join>. On the 15th of June, between eleven and twelve o'clock, I was lying down to sleep on <placeName id="t18200628-177-crimeloc970">Hampstead Heath</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200628-177-crimeloc970" type="placeName" value="Hampstead Heath"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200628-177-crimeloc970" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200628-177-off967 t18200628-177-crimeloc970"></join>, with several more labourers - we had made a tent. I put my jacket over my children for a covering. About two o'clock my eldest child said the kettle was gone; I got up and found it outside the tent, but all our victuals was gone out of it. I missed the jacket and hat, and on Sunday, the 18th, I found the prisoner in the cage with them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200628-177-person1516">
